The paper proposes a novel semi-supervised meta-learning method for few-shot classification, which involves training a few-shot model to predict pseudo labels for unlabeled data and then iteratively self-training on labeled and pseudo-labeled data. This involves techniques from machine learning (meta-learning, semi-supervised learning, few-shot learning), computer vision (ImageNet benchmarks), natural language processing (self-training), and neural networks (soft weighting network). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
